Cell["\<\
So we see that this integral consists on its subcut of a generalized third \
kind differential form on the K3 surface. This differential form has of \
course additional cycles and therefore LSs that we have to remove to obtain a \
canonical integral. 
To see this explicitly, we compute the \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]torus period\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] for this differential form and for this a \
Picard-Fuchs operator.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.982300346509673*^9, 
  3.9823004686257353`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e7210914-0596-4d6e-9d77-\
ec368ba6aace"],

