Cell["\<\
The third kind form on the elliptic curve is just a total derivative.
Therefore, by adding the right boundary constant to this period it is just a \
combination of the first and second kind periods of the elliptic curve.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.982307436101458*^9, 3.9823074462094393`*^9}, {
  3.98230861456956*^9, 
